Admission Appointments
Students can make an appointment to meet in-person with an Admissions Specialist Monday
                        - Thursday, during normal business hours. Current students will be asked to log in
                        as part of the process and prospective students without portal access should use the
                        "Continue as Guest" option in the
EFSC Appointment Scheduler
to request an on-campus appointment.
Document Submission & Drop-Off
You can
review the Accepted Student Information
for tips on completing your admissions requirements. Students are encouraged to send
                        documents to the admissions offices electronically through the Student Document Drop-Box
                        using the following steps:
Log in to myEFSC
Navigate to Student Document Dropbox
Click or tap the Choose File Button to browse your device and choose a PDF document
                           (Repeat this step if you wish to upload multiple documents. Be sure you are choosing
                           documents that you have saved, filled out completely if needed, and signed if required.)
Click or tap the dropdown arrow in the "Send to" field and choose "Admissions"
Once you have verified the correct documents are selected and the "Send to" field
                           shows "Admissions", click or tap the Upload button
Printers and scanners capable of turning your documents into PDFs for submission are
                        available in EFSC’s open computer labs and libraries. You can also scan documents
                        using your Apple or Android Smart Phone. While the online dropbox is a very convenient
                        option, you can drop off physical documents at any Admissions Office during business
                        hours.

Frequently Asked Questions
How do I obtain my Student ID number or Student Email Address?
You can retrieve your Student ID number (B-number) or Titan Student Email address
                                    by
visiting the Student ID and Email Lookup page
.
EFSC students must log in to the myEFSC portal and other applications accessed through
                                    Titan Sign In with their Titan email address and password. That email address was
                                    sent to you when you were accepted to EFSC.
Once logged in you can also retrieve your student ID number by clicking the myGPS
                                    icon to visit the degree self-auditing system and you will see your Student ID listed,
                                    which begins with a "B".
If you are not able to obtain your Student ID number through the online options above,
                                    please
contact the Admissions Office
at any campus.
Because your student ID number is protected information, you cannot receive your number
                                    over the phone. Your records are protected by the Family Education and Privacy Act
                                    of 1974 (FERPA) and will not be provided to anyone other than yourself without written
                                    permission.
To reset a forgotten password,
visit the EFSC Password Reset page
.
If you have questions about your student email address, reach out to
IT Support
at 321-433-7600, seven days a week from 7 AM to midnight.
How do I resume or check the status of my Application for Admissions?
Visit our online admissions application
and enter the email address and password you used to create your application system
                                 account. Once the online application has been submitted, check your email for official
                                 notifications related to your acceptance.
For accepted students
, the Message Center available after logging into myEFSC will include communications
                                 related to outstanding document requirements.
How can I submit an application for Financial Aid?
Visit the federal government's FAFSA website
to submit a Free Application for Federal Student Aid. Please be sure to include EFSC’s
                                    school code, which is 001470 or the site allows you to search for it, to ensure your
                                    application is sent to us.
Approximately two weeks after you have submitted your FAFSA, you may check the status
                                    of your award information through your student portal. If you are not yet a student,
                                    you may
contact any campus financial aid office for the status
.
How can I apply for Scholarships?
Eastern Florida State College offers hundreds of scholarships for EFSC students each
                                    year via Titan Scholarships, many of them funded through the generosity of donors
                                    to the EFSC Foundation. The online Titan Scholarships system is used to advertise
                                    and award scholarships to ensure that scholarships are advertised equitably to all
                                    Eastern Florida students.
You'll also find information about other EFSC scholarships, including department scholarships,
                                    plus information about Bright Futures state scholarships, in the
Financial Aid area of our site
.
How do I register for classes?
Log in to the
myEFSC
portal
Select Titan Web Services
Click on Student Services
Click Registration
Click Add/Drop Classes
Select Term and Click Submit
Enter CRN(s) and Click Submit Changes
OR
Click Class Search
Select appropriate information
Click Class Search
Find your preferred course(s) and check appropriate box
Click Register or Add to Worksheet to add multiple classes at the same time
View more information about
how to register for courses
, including tutorial links.
How do I print my schedule or view my classes?
Log in to the
myEFSC
portal
Select Titan Web Services
Click Student Services
Click Registration
Click Student Detail Schedule or Student Schedule by Day & Time
How do I find an instructor's contact information?
Visit the main
Faculty Web Pages
list and then check the alphabetical list for your instructor’s last name, which
                              will be linked to their current contact information, teaching schedule, and office
                              hours.
How do I drop a class?
To drop a class and get a full tuition refund, you must submit the request by the
                                    established "Last Date to Drop a Class" deadline. See the
Academic Calendar
on the website to see the last day to drop a class.
You may drop a class in person or online. Any tuition paid for a class dropped by
                                    the deadline will be refunded. The course will not appear on your EFSC transcript.
                                    After the drop deadline, you must withdraw from the class, following established procedures.
To drop a course:
Log in to the
myEFSC portal
.
Select Titan Web Services
Click on Student Services
Click on Registration
Click Add/Drop
Select Term and Click Submit
Select courses to be dropped and click Submit Changes
See more
details about dropping a course
, including the difference from withdrawing.
How do I withdraw from a course?
All withdrawals must be submitted by the Academic Calendar's published deadline to
                                    be eligible for the "W" grade. Withdrawal forms must be complete. Students receiving
                                    financial aid or veterans benefits must consult with that office to determine the
                                    effect on benefits. High school students in dual enrollment or early admissions must
                                    first consult with their high school to ensure the withdrawal will have no impact
                                    on their high school graduation.
Get more
withdrawal process details
, including the important differences from dropping a course.
How do I pay for classes online?
Log in to the
­myEFSC
portal
A payment summary and short cut link in the "Pay My Bill" section will be visible
                                          on your student landing page after logging in.
After log in, you can also:
Select Titan Web Services
Click on Student Services
Click on Student Records
Click on Account Summary/Pay Student Account
Click on Click Here to Pay Fees
See more about making payments to EFSC
on the Student Accounts page
.
How can I request an official transcript?
Eastern Florida State College has appointed Credentials Solutions as the designated
                                    agent for printing and mailing academic transcript documents and for sending official
                                    PDF academic transcript documents via the Credentials TranscriptsNetwork™.
Visit EFSC's Transcript Request webpage
for detailed information about the process and how to access the service, which includes
                                    convenient online options, plus information on requests by mail.
How can I obtain an unofficial transcript?
Log in to the myEFSC
portal
Select Titan Web Services
Click on Student Services
Click on Student Records
Click on Academic History Record
You can also
visit the FloridaShines website
and once there in the "Get Started" section, choose "Get a transcript of the courses
                                       you've taken" for an unofficial record.
How can I reset my password?
Visit the EFSC Password Reset page
to reset your login password, also known as your passphrase.
You can also call the IT Support Desk at 321-433-7600 and a Technical Support Agent
                                       will assist with resetting your password. Have your student ID number available. The
                                       IT Support Desk hours are 7 AM to midnight, seven days a week.
When will the College be closed for holidays/breaks?
For college closure times please access the current
Academic Calendar
.

IT Support Desk
The EFSC IT Support Desk serves as the single point of contact between students, faculty
                        and staff and the Information Technologies Department. The IT Support Desk staff will
                        assist you with your questions, requests, and suggestions or route them to the appropriate
                        area for resolution.

Monday through Friday: 7 AM to midnight
Saturday and Sunday: Noon to midnight
Call: 321-433-7600
Submit an IT Ticket for Assistance
Online Resources: Frequently Asked Questions
What is my Student email address and Student ID number?
Your EFSC Titans student email address was sent to you when you were accepted to EFSC.
                                          You must use this student email address, along with your password, to log in to the
                                          myEFSC Portal and other online applications accessed through Titan Sign In.
Your Student Identification Number is your 8-digit number that begins with a capital
                                          "B"
If you do not know your Email Address or Student ID Number,
visit the Email and ID Look-Up page
. You must protect your ID number, as it is your gateway to your student records and
                                          must be listed on certain EFSC forms.
Your Student ID number can also be found once logged in to myEFSC by clicking the
                                          myGPS icon to visit the degree self-audit system where it will be listed.
Visit EFSC's Password Reset page
if you need to reset your login password.
If you are not able to obtain your Student ID number through the online options above,
                                          please contact the Admissions Office at any campus. EFSC faculty and staff should
                                          call Human Resources.
Because your student ID number is protected information, you cannot receive your number
                                          over the phone. Your records are protected by the Family Education and Privacy Act
                                          of 1974 (FERPA) and will not be provided to anyone other than yourself without written
                                          permission.
What is my Password?
Your Password is used to log in to the secure area along with your EFSC email address.
For newly admitted students: initial log-in information related to your password is
                                                included in your acceptance letter and email.
Previously admitted and returning students: your myEFSC password is the password you
                                                last used to log in. If you forgot that password,
visit EFSC's Password Reset page
and click the “Forgot Password” option. You can also use that Titan Sign In self-service
                                                dashboard to reset your password or log in.
If you need assistance with your password, contact IT Support.
How do I access the myEFSC Portal?
myEFSC & Titan Web preferred browser list (latest version):
Google Chrome
Mozilla Firefox
Microsoft Edge
Safari
To Access myEFSC:
Log in to myEFSC
You can also access myEFSC through the Logins dropdown menu at the top of the College
                                          website and inside the drop-down menu on a mobile device.
Username:
Enter your Titan email address.
Password:
Enter your password (same password used for registration, grades, etc.)
myEFSC is Eastern Florida State College's portal that allows students, faculty, and
                                       staff to access all the resources needed to be successful. With one login, you can
                                       access all resources important to your role at the college!
View the Student Services Online Quick Reference Guide
for more tips and information on the services available through myEFSC.
How do I access my Student Email?
Outlook Live is Eastern Florida State College's official student email system.
You can log in through this link
to read and send your EFSC Titans student email.
You can look up your student email address through the
Student ID and Email Look-Up online tool
.
You also may obtain your email ID by
logging into myEFSC
, choosing the TitanWeb icon and selecting the "personal information" link, followed
                                       by the "View Email Addresses/or Network ID" link.
Your email address will also be included in your EFSC acceptance letter.
If you experience further problems, please contact the IT Tech Support Desk at (321)
                                       433-7600 or
submit a ticket through the online IT Support System
.
Visit our student email page
for more information.
How do I access my Canvas account and courses?
After
logging in to your myEFSC account
, locate and click the Canvas icon to gain access. New students will receive a Canvas
                                       account after registering for a course as early as a few weeks prior to the beginning
                                       of a term. Accounts can take up to 24 hours to be created after registering for a
                                       course.
Courses may also start appearing in a Canvas account closer to the beginning of a
                                       term, but they may not be published by the instructor until the first day of class.
                                       After registering for a course, it may take up to 24 hours before the course is available
                                       in the account. You may be able to access the course in the morning hours the following
                                       day.
View this Knowledge Base article
for more details.
For further assistance with Canvas you may:
Contact the IT Support Desk at 321-433-7600 or
submit a ticket through the online IT Support System
.
Select the "Help" link within Canvas and then either select "Search the Canvas Guides"
                                          or "Report a Problem".
Current Canvas system status is available at
https://status.instructure.com
How can I complete the Canvas orientation?
The Canvas Orientation course (PLT-6007) can be found on the Dashboard as soon as
                                       you access your Canvas account and in the Courses menu. This is a separate orientation
                                       course from the general New Student Orientation (TitanPreview). The Canvas Orientation
                                       provides an overview of how to navigate Canvas, communicate with your instructor and
                                       classmates, and submit assignments.
It is important to complete this orientation as soon as possible since it is required
                                       before a student can turn in assignments and appear properly on the instructor’s roster.
                                       After successfully reviewing each Module in the orientation course and clicking the
                                       Finish Orientation button on the last page, the orientation will be complete and full
                                       Student access will be granted for each course a student is registered for.
View this Knowledge Base article
for more details.
How do I log in to a computer on campus?
Students who are currently enrolled may login to student campus computers using the
                                       same Username and Password required for myEFSC (Titan Sign In). Students in a classroom
                                       using a different sign-in method should first contact their instructor for assistance.
Where can I find the current WiFi/Wireless information?
Eastern Florida State College provides campuswide wireless access for staff, faculty,
                                       and students.
Login to myEFSC
to access the current WiFi password.
For questions about WiFi access contact the IT Support Desk at 321-433-7600, open
                                       7am to midnight, seven days a week.
How do I install the Microsoft 365 programs (Word, Excel, PowerPoint, and more)?
Visit this Knowledge Base article
for instructions and other related articles on how to install the Microsoft 365 programs.
Visit our Microsoft 365
web page for general information.
What web browsers are recommended for EFSC systems?
The following browsers are compatible with the EFSC website and various applications.
                                       For the best experience, update to the latest version.
Google Chrome
Microsoft Edge
Mozilla Firefox
Safari
Internet Explorer (IE) is not recommended and is not compatible with Canvas. Microsoft
                                       retired the IE browser and all support for it on June 15, 2022.
You may sometimes need to
clear your browser cache
for the latest version of a page or PDF to load properly.

About EFSC
About EFSC
The Educational Leader on Florida's Space Coast
We see education as a partnership to launch your academic dreams and career goals.
                     That’s why about 18,000 students each year choose to take classes at Eastern Florida
                     State College. Attending a state college makes a big difference to your budget – with
                     tuition and fees that are often half as much as a state university. Bachelor and Associate
                     Degrees, short-term career training certificates that get you ready for the workforce
                     quickly – with so many choices – we’re the perfect place for recent high school graduates.
                     Plus EFSC is also a great match for adults who want to change careers or enhance their
                     workforce skills thanks to our advanced degrees and vocational training.
A History of Excellence
EFSC is recognized as one of America's leading state colleges for quality instruction
                                 and innovative, leading-edge programs. Established in 1960, we've grown and expanded
                                 to serve the Space Coast's educational needs on four campuses plus Eastern Florida
                                 Online. Learn more about our rich history, and the benefits of becoming an EFSC Titan.

                              advanced degrees, in flexible formats that meet the needs of all students, especially
                              working adults who want to climb the career ladder.

Accessibility Statement
Eastern Florida State College is committed to providing inclusive and accessible events.
                     If you require reasonable accommodations due to a disability for an EFSC performance
                     or have questions about event accessibility, please contact SAIL at
SAIL@easternflorida.edu
or 321-433-5939. Requests for appropriate and reasonable accommodations must be made
                     at least five EFSC operating business days (Monday through Thursday) prior to the
                     event. We will attempt to implement accommodation requests but cannot guarantee they
                     can be met by performance dates. All accommodations and services will be determined
                     on a case-by-case basis. If the event is at the King Center for the Performing Arts,
                     please view the
King's Center's accessibility information
.

Student Activities
Student Activities
Your time in college isn't just about academics. It's also about the experiences and
                     memories you create outside of the classroom, and the best way to do that is by engaging
                     in EFSC's vibrant student life on campus. Use our quick links if you know what you're
                     looking for, and be sure to explore below for details.
Titan Virtual Hub
Student Clubs
SGA
Contacts
Get involved through
student clubs and organizations
. There's something for everyone, whether you're interested in politics, the arts,
                     sports, culture, technology, or community service. Clubs are a great way to meet new
                     people who share your interests, gain valuable leadership and organizational skills,
                     and have fun.
The
Titan Virtual Hub
is the best place to get info about on-campus and online events
throughout the year. From concerts to parties to guest speakers, there's always something
                     going on that you won't want to miss! Please note that some events listed on the Hub
                     are sponsored by the Office of Student Life (OSL). OSL-sponsored events are for the
                     benefit of current EFSC students only who are taking at least one class during the
                     term. No others, including children, may attend.
Join the
Student Government Association (SGA)
to help plan events and bring your ideas to life on campus. The SGA represents the
                     student body and serves as a liaison with college administrators. As a member, you
                     can advocate for student interests, plan events and initiatives, and gain valuable
                     leadership experience.
